Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:19.25,英文,,0,0,0,,We have those blue slides, and those might be useful for Build Your Own World.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.43,0:06:19.25,中文,,0,0,0,,我们有那些蓝色幻灯片  它们可能对“构建你自己的世界”有用
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.25,0:06:25.24,英文,,0,0,0,,And we have these white slides, and these will be important for future game development.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.25,0:06:25.24,中文,,0,0,0,,我们还有这些白色幻灯片  这些对未来的游戏开发很重要
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.24,0:06:32.96,英文,,0,0,0,,I'm going to close that. Is it possible to close the black windows there?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.24,0:06:32.96,中文,,0,0,0,,我要关掉它   可以把那边的黑色窗口关掉吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.96,0:06:33.96,英文,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.96,0:06:33.96,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:38.00,英文,,0,0,0,,Let's just see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.96,0:06:38.00,中文,,0,0,0,,让我们看看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:39.78,英文,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.00,0:06:39.78,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:51.10,英文,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:51.10,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.10,0:06:53.50,英文,,0,0,0,,OK, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.10,0:06:53.50,中文,,0,0,0,,好的  让我们看看
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:06:56.01,英文,,0,0,0,,Does the audio still work on Zoom or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.50,0:06:56.01,中文,,0,0,0,,Zoom的音频还能用吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.01,0:06:59.55,英文,,0,0,0,,Can people still hear me in the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.01,0:06:59.55,中文,,0,0,0,,后面的人还能听到我说话吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.55,0:07:06.49,英文,,0,0,0,,OK, I'll probably just hold the mic because, yeah, it's a little bit tiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.55,0:07:06.49,中文,,0,0,0,,好的  我可能就直接拿着麦克风了  是的  有点累
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:12.92,英文,,0,0,0,,In Project 3A, Phase A and B, you created random worlds and you enabled the player to move around the world using keyboards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.49,0:07:12.92,中文,,0,0,0,,在项目3A的A阶段和B阶段  你创建了随机世界  并使玩家能够使用键盘在世界中移动
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:17.52,英文,,0,0,0,,Phase C involves adding new features to make it an actual game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.92,0:07:17.52,中文,,0,0,0,,C阶段包括添加新功能  使其成为一个真正的游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:21.97,英文,,0,0,0,,The key question is, how do you design a good game?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.52,0:07:21.97,中文,,0,0,0,,关键问题是  如何设计一个好的游戏？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.97,0:07:32.87,英文,,0,0,0,,The key concept and the key rationale for making a game good is that you should engage the player, or if you engage them too much, then you can say the game is a little bit addictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.97,0:07:32.87,中文,,0,0,0,,制作好游戏  关键的概念和基本原理是让玩家投入其中  如果玩家过于投入  你甚至可以说这款游戏有点让人上瘾
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.87,0:07:34.89,英文,,0,0,0,,One example here is Flappy Bird.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.87,0:07:34.89,中文,,0,0,0,,举个例子  比如Flappy Bird
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.89,0:07:39.23,英文,,0,0,0,,How many of you have no Flappy Bird played it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.89,0:07:39.23,中文,,0,0,0,,在座有多少人没玩过Flappy Bird？
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:41.84,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.23,0:07:41.84,中文,,0,0,0,,看来玩过的人很多
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:45.82,英文,,0,0,0,,In Flappy Bird, the player's action space is very limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.84,0:07:45.82,中文,,0,0,0,,在Flappy Bird中  玩家的操作空间非常有限
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:48.70,英文,,0,0,0,,There's just one action, which is to tap the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.82,0:07:48.70,中文,,0,0,0,,只有一个操作  就是点击屏幕
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:54.80,英文,,0,0,0,,When you tap the screen, the bird just flies up a little bit and then it falls down due to gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.70,0:07:54.80,中文,,0,0,0,,当你点击屏幕时  小鸟只会向上飞一点  然后就会因为重力而掉下来
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:08:03.59,英文,,0,0,0,,The tricky thing about Flappy Bird is that it's really difficult to time the clicks correctly, and you want to avoid all these pipes and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.80,0:08:03.59,中文,,0,0,0,,Flappy Bird的难点在于  很难掌握点击的时机  而且你要避开所有这些管道之类的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.59,0:08:07.77,英文,,0,0,0,,One takeaway from Flappy Bird is that you want your game mechanics to be very easy to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.59,0:08:07.77,中文,,0,0,0,,Flappy Bird给我们的一点启示是  你的游戏机制要易于学习
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:13.02,英文,,0,0,0,,For example, a very simple and not complex action space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:13.02,中文,,0,0,0,,例如  一个非常简单而不复杂的操作空间
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.02,0:08:21.38,英文,,0,0,0,,But there should be something interesting in your game that makes your actions really hard to master.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.02,0:08:21.38,中文,,0,0,0,,但是你的游戏中应该有一些有趣的东西  让你的操作很难精通
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.38,0:08:23.22,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, you might have this question.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.38,0:08:23.22,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  你可能会问这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:26.23,英文,,0,0,0,,Flappy Bird is a very simple game, only one action space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.22,0:08:26.23,中文,,0,0,0,,Flappy Bird是一个非常简单的游戏  只有一个操作空间
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:29.45,英文,,0,0,0,,What if my game mechanisms are inherently complicated?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.23,0:08:29.45,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我的游戏机制本身就很复杂呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.45,0:08:32.09,英文,,0,0,0,,It isn't very interesting if I just want a player to be able to do one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.45,0:08:32.09,中文,,0,0,0,,如果我只想让玩家能够做一件事  那就没什么意思了
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:35.59,英文,,0,0,0,,They should be able to do four things, ten things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:35.59,中文,,0,0,0,,他们应该能够做四件事  十件事
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:39.96,英文,,0,0,0,,You want a way to make the player learn the mechanisms gradually.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.59,0:08:39.96,中文,,0,0,0,,你需要一种方法让玩家逐渐学习这些机制
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.96,0:08:50.09,英文,,0,0,0,,That's why most of you might have seen in some games that we have tutorial levels, which are explicit textual instructions given by the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.96,0:08:50.09,中文,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么你们大多数人可能在一些游戏中看到过教程关卡  也就是游戏给出的明确的文字说明
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:57.07,英文,,0,0,0,,They might be embedded in an actual level, so you might still have a task, but the game still tells you what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.09,0:08:57.07,中文,,0,0,0,,这些说明可能嵌入在一个实际的关卡中  所以你可能仍然有一个任务  但是游戏仍然会告诉你该做什么
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:09:03.80,英文,,0,0,0,,The game will still tell you, you should activate this switch, or you should open this door or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.07,0:09:03.80,中文,,0,0,0,,游戏仍然会告诉你  你应该启动这个开关  或者你应该打开这扇门什么的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:05.92,英文,,0,0,0,,Here is a tutorial from Genshin Impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.80,0:09:05.92,中文,,0,0,0,,这是来自原神的一个教程
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:15.82,英文,,0,0,0,,As you can see, there are actually levels that let you trigger some sort of an elemental reaction, but the game is telling you, okay, when Pyro meets Dendro, it triggers burning,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.92,0:09:15.82,中文,,0,0,0,,可以看到有一些关卡可以让你触发某种元素反应  但游戏会告诉你  当火遇到草时  它会触发燃烧
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:23.82,英文,,0,0,0,,and then basically it's kind of like reading a textbook or something, just like a miniature version.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.82,0:09:23.82,中文,,0,0,0,,然后基本上就像读教科书或什么的  就像一个微型版本
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:27.69,英文,,0,0,0,,There's one issue with tutorial levels, although they're systematic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.82,0:09:27.69,中文,,0,0,0,,教程关卡虽然系统化  但有一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.69,0:09:30.51,英文,,0,0,0,,Players don't learn by reading text.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.69,0:09:30.51,中文,,0,0,0,,玩家不是通过阅读文本来学习的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.51,0:09:34.07,英文,,0,0,0,,They learn by interacting with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.51,0:09:34.07,中文,,0,0,0,,他们通过与世界互动来学习
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.07,0:09:40.98,英文,,0,0,0,,This is one thing you might have heard of when you're doing your application essay for colleges or something, which is show, don't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.07,0:09:40.98,中文,,0,0,0,,当你写大学申请论文或其他东西时  你可能听说过一句话  那就是“展示  不要说”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:45.36,英文,,0,0,0,,That's why we introduced the concept called an anti-peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:45.36,中文,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么我们引入了“反和平”的概念
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:51.40,英文,,0,0,0,,Anti-peace basically means that you have an innocuous task that precedes a very big challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.36,0:09:51.40,中文,,0,0,0,,反和平基本上意味着你有一个无害的任务  然后是一个非常大的挑战
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:55.44,英文,,0,0,0,,This task is going to hint you at how you could resolve that challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:55.44,中文,,0,0,0,,这个任务会暗示你如何解决这个挑战
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:59.22,英文,,0,0,0,,So let's take a look at the word hint there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:59.22,中文,,0,0,0,,让我们来看看“暗示”这个词
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.22,0:10:04.91,英文,,0,0,0,,The word hint doesn't actually mean the game tells you what to do, but you should figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.22,0:10:04.91,中文,,0,0,0,,暗示这个词并不意味着游戏告诉你该做什么  但你应该自己弄清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:09.33,英文,,0,0,0,,So there are no explicit verbal instructions, and the player should just figure things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:09.33,中文,,0,0,0,,所以没有明确的口头指示  玩家应该自己弄清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:13.97,英文,,0,0,0,,There's another example, Portal 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.33,0:10:13.97,中文,,0,0,0,,还有一个例子  传送门2
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.97,0:10:19.12,英文,,0,0,0,,So this lecture is going to have a lot of concrete examples from various games, because each game just has different elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.97,0:10:19.12,中文,,0,0,0,,这节课将会有很多来自不同游戏的具体例子  因为每个游戏都有不同的元素
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.12,0:10:27.31,英文,,0,0,0,,I'll try to introduce the context for people who never play the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.12,0:10:27.31,中文,,0,0,0,,我会尽量向从未玩过游戏的人介绍背景
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:32.29,英文,,0,0,0,,In Portal 2, the player can place two connecting portals to transport themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:32.29,中文,,0,0,0,,在传送门2中  玩家可以放置两个连接的门户来传送自己
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:37.87,英文,,0,0,0,,They need to use these portals to overcome obstacles.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:37.87,中文,,0,0,0,,他们需要使用这些门户来克服障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:41.33,英文,,0,0,0,,Here is one example level from Portal 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.87,0:10:41.33,中文,,0,0,0,,这是来自传送门2的一个关卡示例
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.33,0:10:44.45,英文,,0,0,0,,You actually have these platforms that are an obstacle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.33,0:10:44.45,中文,,0,0,0,,你实际上有这些平台作为障碍
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:46.65,英文,,0,0,0,,You want to go up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.45,0:10:46.65,中文,,0,0,0,,你想上去这里
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.65,0:10:50.49,英文,,0,0,0,,The height is designed so that the player cannot just jump on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.65,0:10:50.49,中文,,0,0,0,,这个高度设计成玩家不能直接跳到平台上
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:56.97,英文,,0,0,0,,But then you will see that there is an orange portal already created for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.49,0:10:56.97,中文,,0,0,0,,但你会发现那里已经为你创建了一个橙色传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.97,0:11:00.41,英文,,0,0,0,,If you place a blue portal on the wall, actually anywhere, you can even place it on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.97,0:11:00.41,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你在墙上放置一个蓝色传送门  实际上可以在任何地方
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:06.41,英文,,0,0,0,,and you enter that portal, you're actually going to come out of the orange portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.41,0:11:06.41,中文,,0,0,0,,你甚至可以把它放在地板上  然后你进入那个传送门  你实际上会从橙色传送门出来
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:17.29,英文,,0,0,0,,This will actually have the height, and then you're likely going to have some velocity that puts you in a projectile motion, and that takes you on this platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.41,0:11:17.29,中文,,0,0,0,,这实际上会有一定高度  然后你可能会有一些速度  使你进入抛物线运动  然后把你带到这个平台上
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.29,0:11:27.31,英文,,0,0,0,,The key idea here is that this introduces a forward movement out of a portal across a gap to a place you couldn't reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.29,0:11:27.31,中文,,0,0,0,,这里的关键思想是  这引入了从传送门向前移动  跨过一个缺口  到达你无法到达的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:30.27,英文,,0,0,0,,This is some sort of a heuristic when you're playing the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:30.27,中文,,0,0,0,,当你玩游戏时  这是一种启发式方法
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:37.10,英文,,0,0,0,,If you notice this panel here, this is a protruding thrust-forward panel with an orange portal on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.27,0:11:37.10,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你注意到这里的这个面板  这是一个突出的向前推力的面板  上面有一个橙色传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:42.74,英文,,0,0,0,,Whenever you see something like this, you're going to think back to this level and what you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.10,0:11:42.74,中文,,0,0,0,,每当你看到这样的东西  你都会想起这一关和你所做的事情
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.74,0:11:46.10,英文,,0,0,0,,Now comes the real challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.74,0:11:46.10,中文,,0,0,0,,现在真正的挑战来了
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:50.61,英文,,0,0,0,,Here's a room with a larger gap and a deep hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:50.61,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个房间  有一个更大的缺口和一个很深的洞
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:57.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, this black platform here is quite narrow, and the player is likely to fall in the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:57.08,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  这里的黑色平台相当窄  玩家很可能会掉进坑里
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.08,0:12:00.76,英文,,0,0,0,,They cannot go out unless they create a floor portal,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.08,0:12:00.76,中文,,0,0,0,,他们不能出去  除非他们创建一个地板传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.76,0:12:04.76,英文,,0,0,0,, because the game's rule is that these black surfaces, you cannot really create portals on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.76,0:12:04.76,中文,,0,0,0,,因为游戏的规则是  这些黑色表面  你不能真正地在其上创建传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.76,0:12:08.91,英文,,0,0,0,,You have to create them on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.76,0:12:08.91,中文,,0,0,0,,你必须在地板上创建它们
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:11.01,英文,,0,0,0,,This actually sets them up for the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.91,0:12:11.01,中文,,0,0,0,,这实际上为他们设置了解决方案
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.01,0:12:15.33,英文,,0,0,0,,If they just jump in through that portal, they're going to come out of the orange portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.01,0:12:15.33,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们只是跳进那个传送门  他们会从橙色传送门出来
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:19.87,英文,,0,0,0,,This actually brings them back to where they started.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:19.87,中文,,0,0,0,,这实际上让他们回到了起点
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.87,0:12:24.53,英文,,0,0,0,,If they look at this more closely, they'll actually realize something similar to the previous level.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.87,0:12:24.53,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们更仔细地观察  他们实际上会意识到与上一关类似的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.53,0:12:27.06,英文,,0,0,0,,We have this portal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.53,0:12:27.06,中文,,0,0,0,,我们有这个传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:32.48,英文,,0,0,0,,If they recall what they did in the previous level, if you fall into another portal,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.06,0:12:32.48,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们回忆起他们在上一关所做的事情  如果你掉进另一个传送门
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:38.48,英文,,0,0,0,,that will actually give you enough velocity to come out of this, and then that should thrust you out from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.48,0:12:38.48,中文,,0,0,0,,那实际上会给你足够的速度从这里出来  然后那应该把你从这里推出
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:45.03,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if you jump into that blue portal intentionally, this is actually going to make you thrust it to the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:45.03,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  如果你故意跳进那个蓝色传送门  这实际上会让你把它推到另一边
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:50.42,英文,,0,0,0,,So you go here, and then you're on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.03,0:12:50.42,中文,,0,0,0,,这边走  然后就到另一边了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:58.14,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so that's Entei Piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:58.14,中文,,0,0,0,,对  这就是Entei Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:05.74,英文,,0,0,0,,You've seen that Entei Piece is how players learn, but why would the player want to learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:05.74,中文,,0,0,0,,我们已经了解了Entei Piece是玩家学习的方式  但为什么玩家想要学习呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.74,0:13:09.31,英文,,0,0,0,,The key issue is that most people play games because they want to relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.74,0:13:09.31,中文,,0,0,0,,关键问题是大多数人玩游戏是为了放松
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:10.61,英文,,0,0,0,,They don't want to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:10.61,中文,,0,0,0,,他们不想学习
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:17.63,英文,,0,0,0,,They don't want to do another 61b stuff or gaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.61,0:13:17.63,中文,,0,0,0,,他们不想再做61B之类的东西或游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:18.91,英文,,0,0,0,,We want motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:18.91,中文,,0,0,0,,我们需要动力
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:24.77,英文,,0,0,0,,The player needs to be motivated to learn game mechanics, and that's when feedback comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.91,0:13:24.77,中文,,0,0,0,,玩家需要有动力去学习游戏机制  这就是反馈的作用
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:27.93,英文,,0,0,0,,It'll be somewhat similar to what you see in psychology.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.77,0:13:27.93,中文,,0,0,0,,这和你在心理学中看到的内容有些类似
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:30.31,英文,,0,0,0,,You have reinforcement and punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.93,0:13:30.31,中文,,0,0,0,,你有强化和惩罚
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.31,0:13:39.33,英文,,0,0,0,,It's like the behaviorism thing that you did to the rats to make them do some sort of behavior, like electric shocks or food or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.31,0:13:39.33,中文,,0,0,0,,就像你对老鼠做行为主义实验一样  用电击或食物之类的东西让它们做出某种行为
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:42.77,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, the first concept here is positive feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.33,0:13:42.77,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  第一个概念是正反馈
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.77,0:13:50.36,英文,,0,0,0,,It's more like a reward, and basically, when you have positive feedback, the player does well,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.77,0:13:50.36,中文,,0,0,0,,它更像是一种奖励  基本上  当你有正反馈时  玩家表现出色
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.36,0:13:56.36,英文,,0,0,0,,and then they'll gain items, abilities, such that it'll make their game become easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.36,0:13:56.36,中文,,0,0,0,,他们就会获得物品、能力  从而使他们的游戏变得更容易
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.36,0:13:57.70,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, the opposite is also true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.36,0:13:57.70,中文,,0,0,0,,反之亦然
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.70,0:14:01.76,英文,,0,0,0,,If they don't do well, they just don't get those items, so the game is kind of harder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.70,0:14:01.76,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们做得不好  他们就得不到那些物品  所以游戏就会变得更难
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:10.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, if the game becomes easier, they're more likely to do well, and this becomes like a self-reinforcing cycle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.76,0:14:10.31,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  如果游戏变得更容易  他们就更有可能做得更好  这就变成了一个自我强化的循环
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:18.01,英文,,0,0,0,,So, some examples, in most of the multiplayer combat games, the more opponents a player defeats,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.31,0:14:18.01,中文,,0,0,0,,举个例子  在大多数多人战斗游戏中  玩家击败的对手越多  他们获得的资源就越多
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.01,0:14:23.01,英文,,0,0,0,, the more resources they're going to get, and they can purchase more items, which enables them to defeat even more opponents.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.01,0:14:23.01,中文,,0,0,0,,他们可以购买更多的物品  这使得他们能够击败更多的对手
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:28.27,英文,,0,0,0,,So, some example games, League of Legends, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:28.27,中文,,0,0,0,,一些例子游戏  比如英雄联盟
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.27,0:14:31.77,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, here's a question for the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.27,0:14:31.77,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  给观众们一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:36.16,英文,,0,0,0,,What are some problems if positive feedback is too strong in a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:36.16,中文,,0,0,0,,如果正反馈在游戏中太强  会有什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:57.08,英文,,0,0,0,,Think about it for maybe a couple of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:57.08,中文,,0,0,0,,思考几秒钟
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:15:01.90,英文,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.08,0:15:01.90,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.90,0:15:07.31,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm just going to roll back to like the... So we were having these.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.90,0:15:07.31,中文,,0,0,0,,嗯  我想要回到……之前我们讨论的那些
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.31,0:15:08.83,英文,,0,0,0,,So yeah, any answers here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.31,0:15:08.83,中文,,0,0,0,,那么  这里有什么答案吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:14.38,英文,,0,0,0,,What are some problems if positive feedback is too strong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.83,0:15:14.38,中文,,0,0,0,,如果正反馈太强  会有什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.38,0:15:18.19,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they're in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.38,0:15:18.19,中文,,0,0,0,,是的  他们在后面
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:20.25,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so the game gets too easy and boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.19,0:15:20.25,中文,,0,0,0,,所以游戏会变得太容易和无聊
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:21.27,英文,,0,0,0,,That's exactly right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:21.27,中文,,0,0,0,,完全正确
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.27,0:15:27.71,英文,,0,0,0,,You know, if you're at the position where, like, you just don't have to do anything, and then you just win the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.27,0:15:27.71,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道  如果你处于那种什么都不用做就能赢得游戏的位置
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.71,0:15:29.74,英文,,0,0,0,,And the opposite is also kind of true, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.71,0:15:29.74,中文,,0,0,0,,反之亦然  你知道的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:34.44,英文,,0,0,0,,If you made some small mistakes in the beginning, what's gonna happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.74,0:15:34.44,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你在一开始犯了一些小错误  会发生什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.44,0:15:35.66,英文,,0,0,0,,The game just becomes too hard, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.44,0:15:35.66,中文,,0,0,0,,游戏就变得太难了  对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.66,0:15:41.46,英文,,0,0,0,,Because there's, like, the opposite becomes even greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.66,0:15:41.46,中文,,0,0,0,,因为相反的情况变得更严重了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.69,英文,,0,0,0,,So, just as you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:44.69,中文,,0,0,0,,所以  正如你所说
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:53.15,英文,,0,0,0,,If positive feedback is too strong in the game, players who are behind are very hard to catch up, and there's a lot of focus on early game decisions, and the leading players just lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.69,0:15:53.15,中文,,0,0,0,,如果游戏中的正反馈太强  落后的玩家很难追赶  而且游戏会过度关注前期决策  领先的玩家会一直领先
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.15,0:15:55.97,英文,,0,0,0,,There's no interesting things to the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.15,0:15:55.97,中文,,0,0,0,,游戏中就没有有趣的事情了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:59.81,英文,,0,0,0,,So we have a contrary aspect called negative feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.97,0:15:59.81,中文,,0,0,0,,所以我们有一个相反的概念  叫做负反馈
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:07.16,英文,,0,0,0,,When the player does well, the game actually becomes harder by giving them more challenging levels or worse items.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:07.16,中文,,0,0,0,,当玩家表现出色时  游戏实际上会通过给他们更具挑战性的关卡或更差的道具来变得更难
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.16,0:16:14.83,英文,,0,0,0,,You know, things are just more interesting if you have a lot of people in the middle, especially like if you're playing Mario Kart where you're having fun with your games.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.16,0:16:14.83,中文,,0,0,0,,你知道  如果有很多玩家在中间  事情就会更有趣  尤其是当你玩马里奥赛车时  你会玩得很开心
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:23.33,英文,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be really fun if like just one player is ahead of the game and then the rest of the players are just like, you know, just doing their thing or falling behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.83,0:16:23.33,中文,,0,0,0,,如果只有一个玩家领先  而其他玩家只是在做自己的事情或落后  那就没什么意思了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:25.07,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the racing game example.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:25.07,中文,,0,0,0,,是的  就是那个赛车游戏的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.07,0:16:33.97,英文,,0,0,0,,If you're the last place player, you actually have a higher chance to get boosting items or you have like some weapons to knock out the leading players.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.07,0:16:33.97,中文,,0,0,0,,如果你是最后一名  实际上你更有可能获得加速道具  或者你有一些武器可以击倒领先的玩家
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:35.89,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, let's think about the mirror question here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.97,0:16:35.89,中文,,0,0,0,,现在  让我们思考一下关于这个问题的反面
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:47.72,英文,,0,0,0,,What are some problems when negative feedback is too strong in a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.89,0:16:47.72,中文,,0,0,0,,当负反馈在游戏中过强时  会有什么问题？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:49.86,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.72,0:16:49.86,中文,,0,0,0,,是吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:54.20,英文,,0,0,0,,Sorry, can you repeat that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.86,0:16:54.20,中文,,0,0,0,,抱歉  你能重复一遍吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:57.44,英文,,0,0,0,,So that's a great thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.20,0:16:57.44,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个很好的想法
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.44,0:16:59.57,英文,,0,0,0,,So you said it's going to become too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.44,0:16:59.57,中文,,0,0,0,,你说游戏会变得太难了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:08.55,英文,,0,0,0,,So what I'm going to point out here is that when the player actually doesn't do that well, the game is actually trying to help them by making the game length easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.57,0:17:08.55,中文,,0,0,0,,我要指出的是  当玩家表现不佳时  游戏实际上试图通过降低游戏难度来帮助他们
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.55,0:17:12.87,英文,,0,0,0,,So I wouldn't say it's necessarily becoming too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.55,0:17:12.87,中文,,0,0,0,,我不会说它一定会变得太难
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.87,0:17:17.38,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.87,0:17:17.38,中文,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.24,英文,,0,0,0,,Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.38,0:17:18.24,中文,,0,0,0,,是的  没错
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.24,0:17:25.19,英文,,0,0,0,,So there's no motivation for you to get better, because even if you just don't do well, you can just rely on the game giving you good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.24,0:17:25.19,中文,,0,0,0,,你就没有动力去提高自己  因为即使你表现不好  你也可以依靠游戏给你好东西
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:30.21,英文,,0,0,0,,I think some people will just complain to me when they play League of Legends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.19,0:17:30.21,中文,,0,0,0,,我想有些人玩英雄联盟的时候会向我抱怨
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.21,0:17:34.29,英文,,0,0,0,,When they win, the game tends to give them worse teammates, so they lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.21,0:17:34.29,中文,,0,0,0,,当他们赢的时候  游戏往往会给他们更差的队友  所以他们输了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.29,0:17:36.87,英文,,0,0,0,,And then if they lose, the game just gives them better teammates.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.29,0:17:36.87,中文,,0,0,0,,如果他们输了  游戏就会给他们更好的队友
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.87,0:17:41.58,英文,,0,0,0,,So their win rate just stays at 50%, no matter what the skills are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.87,0:17:41.58,中文,,0,0,0,,所以他们的胜率始终保持在50%  无论他们的技术如何
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:47.97,英文,,0,0,0,,So if the player sees that, well, they're just not going to hone their skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.58,0:17:47.97,中文,,0,0,0,,如果玩家看到这一点  他们就不会磨练自己的技术了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:57.28,英文,,0,0,0,,Now, one thing you might notice is that these type of negative feedbacks are actually better suited for party games, where people shouldn't be judged on their skill or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.97,0:17:57.28,中文,,0,0,0,,你可能会注意到  这类负反馈实际上更适合聚会游戏  在这些游戏中  人们不应该以他们的技术或其他东西来评判
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.28,0:17:59.02,英文,,0,0,0,,They just want to have fun together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.28,0:17:59.02,中文,,0,0,0,,他们只是想一起玩得开心
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.02,0:18:01.54,英文,,0,0,0,,So you might see Mario Kart have more of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.02,0:18:01.54,中文,,0,0,0,,你可能会看到像马里奥赛车这样的游戏更多一些
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:10.23,英文,,0,0,0,,Whereas positive feedback is more like competitive games, maybe like Starcraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:10.23,中文,,0,0,0,,而正反馈更像是竞技游戏  比如星际争霸
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:14.17,英文,,0,0,0,,And speaking of motivation, there's actually another problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.23,0:18:14.17,中文,,0,0,0,,说到动机  其实还有另一个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.17,0:18:21.44,英文,,0,0,0,,The player knows everything after a successful run, so the game just becomes very boring because you know all the tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.17,0:18:21.44,中文,,0,0,0,,玩家在一次成功通关后就知道了所有的事情  所以游戏变得非常无聊  因为你已经知道了所有的技巧
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.44,0:18:25.09,英文,,0,0,0,,So you need a variability of game experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.44,0:18:25.09,中文,,0,0,0,,所以你需要游戏体验的多样性
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.09,0:18:26.74,英文,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of ways you can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.09,0:18:26.74,中文,,0,0,0,,有很多方法可以做到这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.74,0:18:33.42,英文,,0,0,0,,You can randomize each run by randomizing items, rooms, or you could just keep on adding new content.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.74,0:18:33.42,中文,,0,0,0,,你可以通过随机分配物品、房间来随机分配每次运行  或者你可以不断添加新内容
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:36.62,英文,,0,0,0,,I put some examples of games who tries to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.42,0:18:36.62,中文,,0,0,0,,我举了一些尝试这样做的游戏的例子
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.62,0:18:40.07,英文,,0,0,0,,This is a game where the rooms are randomly placed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.62,0:18:40.07,中文,,0,0,0,,这是一个房间随机放置的游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.07,0:18:42.77,英文,,0,0,0,,This is just one possible configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.07,0:18:42.77,中文,,0,0,0,,这只是一个可能的配置
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:43.75,英文,,0,0,0,,The boss is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.77,0:18:43.75,中文,,0,0,0,,老板在这里
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.75,0:18:44.83,英文,,0,0,0,,It could be somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.75,0:18:44.83,中文,,0,0,0,,它可能在别的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.83,0:18:47.65,英文,,0,0,0,,This game is called Binding of Isaac.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.83,0:18:47.65,中文,,0,0,0,,这个游戏叫做以撒的结合
